term: Haemoglobin A1c level - International Federation of Clinical Chemistry and Laboratory Medicine standardised
HbA1c level (Diabetes Control and Complications Trial aligned)
Haemoglobin A1c between 7%-10% indicating borderline diabetic control
HbA1 level (Diabetes Control and Complications Trial aligned)
Haemoglobin A1c less than 7% indicating good diabetic control
Haemoglobin A1c greater than 10% indicating poor diabetic control
Hb A1c (Haemoglobin A1c) level - IFCC (International Federation of Clinical Chemistry and Laboratory Medicine) standardised
Hb A1c (Haemoglobin A1c) measurement - IFCC (International Federation of Clinical Chemistry and Laboratory Medicine) standardised
